# Compiled Go binaries (build artifacts — `go run`/`go build` output).
# Each module's binary is named after its folder (examples, exercises, solutions,
# bugged, fixed, server, ...). They are not source and must never be committed.
# These patterns match an extension-less executable that shares its dir name.
day*/examples/examples
day*/exercises/exercises
day*/solutions/solutions
**/debugging/bugged/bugged
**/debugging/fixed/fixed
debugging-challenges/**/bugged/bugged
debugging-challenges/**/fixed/fixed
**/examples/server

# Generic Go build artifacts
*.exe
*.test
*.out

# macOS junk
.DS_Store